column1: # Below are field gradients for each  magnetic beam rigidity (Brho)
# Format of data described as follows:
#  (Lines starting with # are comments. Values are comma delimited.)
# First non-comment row is string that signifies format version
# Next row has column names and Brho values [T-m] corresponding to field settings
# Rows that follow have element name; radii R [m]; n-multipole order; currents at Brho1; Brho2; etc.
# Definition of gradient:  GRAD = B-field/R^(n-1)  =>  field gradient [T/m^(n-1)]; n=1 dipole; n=2 quad; etc.
#       R = bend radius for n=1; multipole reference radius R for n>1   (referred to as pole-tip radius in COSY manual)
# name; radius; multipole order; Brho1; Brho2; etc.
